# Language and simplicity

- Write everything in **English**: code, identifiers, comments, log messages,
  commit messages, and docs. No Portuguese in the codebase.
- Prefer the **smallest change** that solves the problem and preserves functionality.
- Avoid overengineering and over-coding:
  - No new abstraction, interface, or design pattern unless it is needed right now.
  - No new dependency, framework, or config option when the current stack already works.
  - Do not add speculative "future-proof" code.
- Only comment non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints. Do not narrate the code.

```java
// BAD: needless indirection for a single caller
interface Greeter { String greet(String n); }
class DefaultGreeter implements Greeter { public String greet(String n){ return "hi "+n; } }

// GOOD
String greet(String name) { return "hi " + name; }
```
